tent. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig02f">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig03a.jpeg" height="1344" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig03a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig03b.jpeg" height="1325" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig03b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig03c.jpeg" height="1334" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig03c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig04.jpeg" height="1378" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig04" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4</span> SFT of the pancreas in a 70-year-old man. Axial contrast-enhanced CT scan, obtained in the arterial phase, shows a well-defined hypervascular mass with intense enhancement (arrow) in the pancreatic tail.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig04">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig05.jpeg" height="1266" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig05" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5</span> SFT of the sigmoid colon in a 53-year-old woman. Axial contrast-enhanced CT scan shows a het-erogeneously enhancing mass (arrows) in the midline pelvis. The mass compresses the rectosigmoid <i>(S)</i> and displaces it to the left side. Surgical excision was performed; results of histopathologic analysis confirmed the diagnosis of SFT arising from the sigmoid colon.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig05">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig06.jpeg" height="1384" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig06" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6</span> SFT of the mesentery in a 66-year-old man. Coronal contrast-enhanced CT scan shows a large mass (arrows) in the upper right abdomen that involves the small bowel mesentery. The mass has heterogeneous enhancement with multiple nonenhancing areas. Surgical excision was performed; results of histopathologic analysis confirmed the diagnosis of SFT.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig06">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig07a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1588" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig07a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig07b.jpeg" height="1800" width="1600" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig07b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig08a.jpeg" height="1305" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig08a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig08b.jpeg" height="1287" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig08b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig09.jpeg" height="1274" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> Retroperitoneal SFT in a 52-year-old man. Axial contrast-enhanced CT scan shows a heterogeneously enhancing mass (arrows) in the lower abdomen. The mass contains areas of necrosis, which appear as areas of low attenuation.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig10a.jpeg" height="1320" width="1710" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig10b.jpeg" height="1369" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig11.jpeg" height="1218" width="1692" aria-labelledby="fig11" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11</span> SFT of the pelvis in a 56-year-old man. Axial contrast-enhanced CT scan, obtained in the arterial phase, shows a heterogeneously enhancing mass (arrows) in the midline pelvis with areas of nonenhancement (arrowhead), a finding consistent with necrosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig11">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig12a.jpeg" height="1306" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig12a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig12b.jpeg" height="1278" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig12b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig13a.jpeg" height="1400" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.312105080&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.312105080/asset/images/105080fig13b.jpeg" height="1383" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core